  "prompt": "The village people of India did not able to change their currency so what they do?",
  "response": "During the demonetization of \u20b9500 and \u20b91000 notes in November 2016, rural and village people in India faced significant challenges in exchanging their old currency. Here are some strategies they adopted:\n\n1. Barter system\n- Exchanged goods and services directly\n- Traded agricultural products\n- Helped each other in temporary financial arrangements\n\n2. Using local networks\n- Borrowed money from relatives and friends\n- Took loans from local money lenders\n- Relied on community support\n\n3. Alternative payment methods\n- Used mobile payment apps\n- Conducted transactions through bank accounts\n- Used digital payment platforms like Paytm\n\n4. Cooperative approaches\n- Villagers pooled their resources\n- Helped each other exchange limited amounts of currency\n- Shared transportation costs to reach banks\n\n5. Agriculture and daily wage adjustments\n- Delayed purchases\n- Postponed non-essential expenses\n- Adjusted agricultural activities\n\n6. Bank assistance\n- Stood in long queues to exchange currency\n- Sought help from bank officials\n- Used Jan Dhan accounts for transactions\n\nThese strategies highlighted rural communities' resilience and adaptability during a challenging economic transition period.",
